[executed] The two-field row (missing description) and the four-field row each cause parseRow to throw a RowError before any field is read, and tryParseRow returns {ok:false}. No partial entry, defaulted/empty field, or field-shifted entry is produced — the field-count check runs first, so the amount can never be silently read from the description's position.
$ node -e parseRow/tryParseRow on ["2026-01-31","-42.50"] and ["2026-01-31","a","b","-42.50"]
2 fields [date, amount] => THREW RowError: expected exactly 3 fields [date, description, amount], got 2
4 fields => THREW RowError: expected exactly 3 fields ..., got 4
tryParseRow 2-field: {"ok":false,"error":"... got 2"}
tryParseRow 4-field: {"ok":false,"error":"... got 4"}
